obo:ECO_0007695  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_696  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: 25/5/2017 Pim\nTRIM3 was picked up in this paper as a protein with E3-ligase activity (Fig.3) that regulates the protein levels of Shank1A/GKAP (Fig.1). TRIM3 regulates the synaptic (authors have measured GKAP densities/spots around dendritic segments indicative of PSDs localized on dendritic spines) levels of GKAP in a neuronal activity (TTX, bicuculine) dependent manner (Fig.4). Likewise, perturbation of TRIM3 results in change of dendritic spine morphology (GKAP mislocalized and is a scaffolding protein of the PSD; Fig.5). the This could be used for BP annotation against term:\n\n'ubiquitin protein ligase activity (GO:0061630)' regulates 'protein catabolic process (GO:0030163)' occurs_in 'postsynapse (GO:0098794)'\n\nFrom CC annotation in ticket #509\nFig. 2c: biochemical fractionation shows TRIM3 synaptic enrichment.\nFig. 2d: TRIM3 is localized at postsynaptic site\n\nLitteral:\n\"Subcellular fractionation of rat forebrain showed TRIM3 to be particularly abundant in the light membrane fraction (P3), and sparse in the cytosol (S3) (Figure 2C). TRIM3 was also present in the Triton X-100-resistant PSD fractions (PSDI and PSD II), which corroborates its detection in the PSD by mass spectrometry [22]. However, TRIM3 is not enriched in the PSD like PSD-95 and is extracted by Sarkosyl detergent (PSDIII), indicating that TRIM3 is not tightly associated with the PSD (Figure 2B).\n\nBy immunostaining, TRIM3 was widely distributed in a micropunctate pattern throughout the cell body, axon, and dendrites of cultured hippocampal neurons (Figure 2C)\". Experimental description: Fig.1: \"The GFP-Shank1A plasmid was cotransfected into primary **rat** hippocampal neurons (DIV 14)\" + RNAi KD\nFig.3: \"COS-7 cells were cotransfected with a plasmid expressing an epitope-tagged target protein (either GKAP, Shank1A, Shank2, or PSD-95) and either an empty vector (Control) or a FLAG-tagged E3 ligase (**rat** TRIM3, TRIM9, or human Mdm2).\"\nFig.4: \"**Rat** hippocampal neurons were transfected at DIV14 with β-galactosidase (β-gal) and either empty vector, wildtype TRIM3, or TRIM3/264 ...\" (FLAG-TRIM3 is rat species)\nFig.5: also rat neurons and rat FLAG-TRIM3" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2018-04-30" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_696" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

